[{"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-10T23:32:01+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Google TV interface showing a preview of Antiques Roadshow\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/My-adeDP0PS99N41hl156nlzYMo=/0x0:843x562/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73399873/Google_TV_Free_channels_TV.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>People are watching this stuff, and advertisers can now buy targeted ads on Google TV channels.</em> | Image: Google</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"xhQNSi\">Google is <a href=\"https://blog.google/products/ads-commerce/meet-the-google-tv-network/\">launching a new advertising network</a> that serves targeted ads to Google TV-powered streaming boxes and smart TVs. The ads service, known as the Google TV network, lets advertisers place unskippable in-stream ad spots across more than 125 live channels \u2014 many that are FAST, or free ad-supported streaming TV channels that <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/12/6/23990561/google-is-hell-bent-on-getting-you-to-notice-its-free-tv-channels\">Google\u2019s been hel", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/10/24175676/google-fast-ads-streaming-tv-network", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Google is ready to fill free streaming TV channels with ads", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-10T23:08:39+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A screenshot from Star Wars Outlaws\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/77oMPZ9sOZVzzgDQzytRSHNe8gM=/100x0:1180x720/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73267171/sw_outlaws_gameplay_gallery_stormtroopers_80c0d945.5.jpeg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The open-world </em>Outlaws<em> could be the biggest single-player </em>Star Wars<em> game ever made.</em> | Screenshot: Star Wars</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"aMYaJk\">Ubisoft <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24121150/star-wars-outlaws-trailer-release-date\">announced in April</a> that <em>Star Wars Outlaws</em> will launch on the PlayStation 5, Xbox Series X/S, and PC on August 30th. If you\u2019ve been on the fence about buying it in advance, then there\u2019s some new material to help you make the decision. We recently got a <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24172134/star-wars-outlaws-trailer-ubisoft-forward-2024\">closer look at its open-world gameplay</a> at Ubisoft Forward 2024, including the titl", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24125268/star-wars-outlaws-preorder-guide-bonus-skins-dlc-missions-extras-deal", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Where to preorder Star Wars Outlaws (and what\u2019s included in each edition)", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-10T22:42:45+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/5c_qsn-PvV-TamRPrrieq0tSNdQ=/138x0:2520x1588/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73399826/apple_record_transcribe_phone_calls.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Apple</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"ZIySWI\">Apple will let you record and transcribe phone calls in iOS 18. The company announced the feature during its <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/10/24171999/apple-wwdc-2024-news-rumors-announcements-ios-18-ai\">Worldwide Developers Conference on Monday</a> and says it will automatically tell call participants that they\u2019re being recorded.</p>\n<p id=\"eJ85VZ\">The image shared by Apple shows a new recording option on the Phone app, which displays a soundwave, along with how long you\u2019ve been recording. It then transcribes your call in the Notes app, where you can generate a summary using the <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/10/24175405/wwdc-apple-ai-news-features-ios-18-macos-15-iphone-ipa", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/10/24175684/ios-18-record-calls-privacy-apple-intelligence", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "iOS 18 will let you record calls \u2014 and tells everyone for their privacy", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-10T19:59:45+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A screenshot from the video game Assassin\u2019s Creed Shadows.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/77AEIH6gzlApg42ayZO7TMa5MwE=/300x0:3540x2160/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73399574/ACSH_Screenshot_2_Announce_15052024_6PM_CEST.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Ubisoft</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"KlN0KA\">The <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24155451/assassins-creed-shadows-release-date-trailer-ubisoft\">reveal of <em>Assassin\u2019s Creed Shadows</em></a> mostly focused on its story, characters, and setting. But a new trailer gives a better idea of how the game will actually play. The lengthy gameplay overview, which clocks in at around 12 minutes long, shows off the game\u2019s sprawling rendition of Japan, while also detailing the different skills and approaches of its two playable leads. It\u2019s also <em>very</em> bloody.</p>\n<p id=\"FXMPY3\">This is the game\u2019s second gameplay trailer in as many days. Ubisoft also released a shorter clip du", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24172151/assassins-creed-shadows-gameplay-trailer-ubisoft-forward-2024", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Here\u2019s 12 minutes of Assassin\u2019s Creed Shadows gameplay", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-10T19:55:32+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Red artwork of the Adobe brand logo\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/wVCxNyy9mRF_iYPKW-Pk-wBTyqw=/0x0:3000x2000/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73399568/acastro_STK124_03.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Alex Castro / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"rRD0Vc\">Adobe is overhauling the terms customers must agree to when using its apps in an effort to win back trust \u2014 and clarify that it won\u2019t train AI on their work. The change, announced via <a href=\"https://blog.adobe.com/en/publish/2024/06/10/updating-adobes-terms-of-use\">a new blog post</a>, comes after a week of <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/7/24173838/adobe-tos-update-firefly-generative-ai-trust\">backlash from users</a> who feared that an update to Adobe\u2019s terms of service would allow their work to be used for AI training.</p>\n<p id=\"exhnMr\">The new terms of service are expected to roll out on June 18th and aim to better clarify what Adobe is per", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/10/24175416/adobe-overhauls-terms-of-service-update-firefly", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Adobe overhauls terms of service to say it won\u2019t train AI on customers\u2019 work", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-10T19:14:35+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A screenshot from the video game Star Wars Outlaws.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/GZtdqWv3OMH4zQ0VWK_D05Jj_JA=/300x0:3540x2160/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73399509/SWO_Screenshots_CapturedInEngine_Akiva_Action_WIDE.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Ubisoft</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"gz3oAE\">We\u2019re getting very close to the launch of <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24121150/star-wars-outlaws-trailer-release-date\"><em>Star Wars Outlaws</em></a>, Ubisoft\u2019s <em>GTA</em>-style take on a galaxy far, far away. Which means it\u2019s a good time for another trailer detailing the sorts of criminal escapades players can get into. The new overview focused primarily on the different <em>Star Wars</em> locations you\u2019ll be exploring, and along with the various not-exactly-legal missions you\u2019ll take on. Among various aspects featured are dealing with the Hutts, riding a speederbike, and finding new recruits for your scoundrel gang.</p>", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24172134/star-wars-outlaws-trailer-ubisoft-forward-2024", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Star Wars Outlaws gameplay trailer shows off a life of intergalactic crime", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-10T18:57:20+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"An image showing Tim Cook during WWDC 2024\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/njPWSGIvUSCmg4dLurv1zWBTN7U=/57x0:2046x1326/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73399466/timcook_wwdc_2024.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Screenshot: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"aUSycr\">Apple\u2019s Worldwide Developers Conference keynote has come to a close \u2014 and the company had a whole lot to share. We got our first look at the AI features coming to Apple\u2019s devices and some major updates across the company\u2019s operating systems.</p>\n<p id=\"yRjRkZ\">If you missed out on watching the keynote live, we\u2019ve gathered all the biggest announcements that you can check out below.</p>\n<h2 id=\"BKc232\"><a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/10/24175405/wwdc-apple-ai-news-features-ios-18-macos-15-iphone-ipad-mac\">Apple\u2019s first AI system is coming to the iPhone, iPad, and Mac</a></h2>\n  <figure class=\"e-image\">\n        \n      <cite>Screenshot: Apple</cite>\n  </figure", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24171190/apple-wwdc-2024-biggest-announcements", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Apple WWDC 2024: the 13 biggest announcements", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-10T18:54:38+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/VMMoZiAtLil2_nxL9dPcV0Y7TgY=/0x0:2700x1800/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73399462/247088_Roborock_vs_DreameBot_JTuohy_0010.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Support for robot vacuums is coming to Apple Home with iOS18.</em> | Photo by Jennifer Pattison Tuohy / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"7ipNu0\">Apple has announced that Apple Home will finally support robot vacuums with iOS 18. This was one of just a few updates to Apple Home announced at WWDC 2024. The others were guest access for door locks and hands-free unlocking, plus a new electricity usage feature in the Home app, which is limited to Pacific Gas &amp; Electric in California at launch.</p>\n<p id=\"JbPM5d\">Apple didn\u2019t provide many details about robot vacuums in the Home app, only <a href=\"https://www.apple.com/newsroom/2024/06/updates-to-the-home-experience-elevate-entertainment-and-bring-more-convenience/\">stating in a press ", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/10/24172054/apple-home-homekit-robot-vacuum-support-smart-locks-wwdc24", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Apple Home adds support for robot vacuums", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-10T18:39:09+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A photo of Apple\u2019s custom \u201cGenmoji\u201d in iOS 18.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/3mGVHs1-jQx0rwveum41A2hs3Ek=/3x0:1997x1329/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73399451/lcimg_4c0d5da9_6982_41d1_a424_7c05368d2ffe.0.jpeg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo: Allison Johnson / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"1aZMoR\">Apple\u2019s new <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/10/24175405/wwdc-apple-ai-news-features-ios-18-macos-15-iphone-ipad-mac\">\u201cApple Intelligence\u201d</a> AI features will let you make your own custom emoji and images, the company announced at WWDC 2024.</p>\n<p id=\"VxOAYA\">The custom emoji are called \u201cGenmoji,\u201d and they look like a lot of fun. In one example, during Monday\u2019s keynote, Apple showed how the prompt \u201csmiley relaxing wearing cucumbers\u201d generates a yellow smiley face emoji with cucumbers over its eyes. If you don\u2019t like the initial emoji that Apple makes, you can swipe to pick from a few different options.</p>\n<p id=\"", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/10/24175523/apple-ai-custom-emoji-images-ios18-wwdc", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Apple\u2019s AI can make custom emoji and images", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-10T18:38:17+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A slide of Apple announcing ChatGPT in Siri during its WWDC 2024 keynote.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/tIzhMgU4dvwtUZZtLJP_XKcKeXg=/3x0:1997x1329/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73399447/lcimg_200f2853_fa8c_41a9_a669_80504603fff3.5.jpeg\" />\n        <figcaption>Apple announcing ChatGPT in Siri at WWDC 2024. | Allison Johnson / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"sD5ds7\">Apple is partnering with OpenAI to put ChatGPT into Siri, the company announced at its <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/10/24171999/apple-wwdc-2024-news-rumors-announcements-ios-18-ai\">WWDC 2024 keynote</a> on Monday.</p>\n<p id=\"bhpIE4\">ChatGPT will be available for free <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/10/24172132/apple-ios-18-new-features-ai\">in iOS 18</a> and <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/10/24170586/macos-15-mac-apple-ai-wwdc-2024\">macOS Sequoia</a> later this year without an account, and Apple says that user queries won\u2019t be", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/10/24174786/apple-openai-partnership-chatgpt-wwdc", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Apple is putting ChatGPT in Siri for free later this year", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-10T18:36:57+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Mac app, passwords\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/9JdH-CT7fhxOfsFinRkzJIGe7Kk=/122x0:1406x856/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73399445/lcimg_11ca1204_67f3_40b3_81b4_e9423b01662a.0.jpeg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Apple\u2019s new Passwords app.</em> | Image: Apple</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"qXI2Q3\">At <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/10/24171999/apple-wwdc-2024-news-rumors-announcements-ios-18-ai\">WWDC 2024</a>, Apple revealed a new Passwords app that expands on its existing iCloud Keychain features and syncs your passwords across more devices. Now, <a href=\"https://www.apple.com/newsroom/2024/06/macos-sequoia-takes-productivity-and-intelligence-on-mac-to-new-heights/#:~:text=next-,The%20New%20Passwords%20App%20Keeps%20Credentials%20Secure%20and%20Organized,-Built%20on%20the\">with Passwords</a>, Apple is releasing a standalone app to manage passwords and passkeys on more devices, including Apple\u2019s Vision Pro headset, as ", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/10/24175505/apple-password-app-passkey-manager-windows-mac-icloud", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Apple\u2019s standalone Passwords app syncs across iOS, iPad, Mac, and Windows", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-10T18:35:25+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Siri logo on a black background\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/RqfvJvitOGa4txUuE6nwkav31m0=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73399441/acastro_180510_1777_siri_0001.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Alex Castro / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"bQWMlx\">Apple has announced several AI-powered features coming to its Siri virtual assistant, such as an updated design, improvements to how it speaks and understands spoken language commands, and an integration with OpenAI\u2019s ChatGPT model. </p>\n<p id=\"8CJvio\">Some of these features, announced during Apple\u2019s <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/10/24173603/wwdc-2024-live-blog-apple-event-ios-18-ai\">WWDC event on June 10th</a>, come courtesy of Apple Intelligence \u2014 the company\u2019s new privacy-focused personal intelligence system, which the company says will be able to control actions in apps on behalf of users. For Siri, Apple says these actions include ", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/10/24171936/apple-siri-ai-update-ios18-features-wwdc", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Apple is giving Siri an AI upgrade in iOS 18", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-10T18:11:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/agWBbGsdwX9x_C_GDTuNbyT5dCs=/122x0:1406x856/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73399403/lcimg_ca61fcb8_ae16_4dcb_8b5a_e5ca6510cfad.0.jpeg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Apple</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"tiFKil\">Apple announced \u201cApple Intelligence\u201d at <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/apple-wwdc\">WWDC 2024</a>, its name for a new suite of AI features for the iPhone, Mac, and more. </p>\n<p id=\"hsJlQs\">The company that once refused to use the term \u201cartificial intelligence\u201d when talking about its machine learning features now has AI enhancements across its platforms. The company has been behind companies like Google and Microsoft, which started racing ahead with their own generative AI features as soon as OpenAI broke thApple Intelligence at dam open in 2022. Now, it\u2019s making its bid to catch up.</p>\n<h2 id=\"A85vDC\">Apple Intelligence will take action for you in apps</h2>\n<p id=\"eljEpb\">Apple said it", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/10/24175405/wwdc-apple-ai-news-features-ios-18-macos-15-iphone-ipad-mac", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Apple Intelligence: every new AI feature coming to the iPhone and Mac", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-10T18:06:25+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/yMIi4aIcSxWR2bBTwUqV4AOrSns=/122x0:1406x856/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73399374/lcimg_ee086f08_ab2f_44cb_b58c_23e993719781.0.jpg\" />\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"PFdM3j\">Apple\u2019s tvOS doesn\u2019t get the primary focus at WWDC, but it\u2019s still <a href=\"https://www.apple.com/newsroom/2024/06/updates-to-the-home-experience-elevate-entertainment-and-bring-more-convenience/\">adding a few new features</a> this fall, including one that will be familiar to people who\u2019ve used Amazon\u2019s streaming service.</p>\n<p id=\"zPjiUj\">The new InSight feature is limited to Apple TV Plus original shows and movies, where it will show details about the actors and characters on screen, as well as pull up details about the show\u2019s soundtrack so you can add tracks to Apple Music. Amazon\u2019s <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2022/7/18/23268285/amazon-prime-video-2022-redesign-preview-announcement\">similar X-Ray feature</a> began its life on", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/10/24175423/apple-tv-plus-features-tvos-wwdc", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Apple\u2019s InSight feature for Apple TV Plus will tell you who that actor is", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-10T17:05:54+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"iPhone running resident evil 7, first person view with hands defensively held out against an enemy,\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/uu9AWJvD6Ut10m6TiD2Yg_dO4Sg=/0x0:3321x2214/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73399206/Screenshot_2024_06_10_at_11.48.18_AM__2_.0.jpeg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Scary good looking, on an iPhone.</em> | Image: Capcom</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"73gtTq\">Capcom is about to launch <em>Resident Evil 7: Biohazard</em> \u2014 the first game in the survival horror franchise\u2019s shift to a first-person perspective \u2014 for Apple devices. It will be available in the Apple App Store on July 2nd for the iPhone 15 Pro and iPhone 15 Pro Max, as well as iPads and Macs equipped with M-Series chips. <em>RE7</em> originally launched <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2017/1/23/14353714/resident-evil-7-biohazard-review-ps4-xbox-one-pc\">on consoles in 2017</a>.</p>\n<p id=\"ESu020\"><em>RE7</em> for iOS and macOS comes after the s", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/10/24175360/resident-evil-7-biohazard-re7-apple-mac-iphone-ipad-ios", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Resident Evil 7 is making its way to the iPhone, iPad, and Mac", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-10T16:49:38+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A Nutrisense starter kit on a bathroom counter.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/01Juz9JH0NWSKtgHv9qZPhsPrXg=/0x0:2550x1700/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73399150/236730_Nutrisense_glucose_monitor_AKrales_0011.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Unlike the FreeStyle Libre systems (pictured above), Abbott\u2019s new continuous glucose monitors won\u2019t require a prescription.</em> | Photo by Amelia Holowaty Krales / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"xqnglD\">Abbott <a href=\"https://abbott.mediaroom.com/2024-06-10-Abbott-Receives-U-S-FDA-Clearance-for-Two-New-Over-the-Counter-Continuous-Glucose-Monitoring-Systems#assets_2429_124654-111\">announced today</a> that the US Food and Drug Administration has cleared two new over-the-counter continuous glucose monitors (CGM). The Lingo is designed for health-conscious consumers who want to get greater insight into their metabolism. Meanwhile, the Libre Rio is designed for Type 2 diabetics who", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/10/24175352/abbott-lingo-libre-rio-fda-cgm-diabetes-wearables", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Abbott gets FDA clearance for over-the-counter continuous glucose monitors", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-10T16:49:27+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A green Echo Pop smart speaker on a countertop with its light on.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/BZHJS09cWxo1OO_Jox2Y9gSBDWA=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73399147/236685_Amazon_Echo_Pop_JTuohy_0008.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>I\u2019d probably be boring and buy it in black, but more speakers should come in fun colors.</em> | Photo by Jennifer Pattison Tuohy / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"zgVhAC\">The <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23742395/amazon-echo-pop-smart-speaker-review\"><strong>Echo Pop</strong></a> is the cheapest and simplest way into Amazon\u2019s smart home ecosystem, and the tiny Alexa-enabled smart speaker is on sale for just $19.99 ($20 off) at <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Introducing-sound-compact-speaker-Midnight/dp/B09WNK39JN?tag=theverge02-20\" rel=\"sponsored nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Amazon</a>, <a href=\"https://howl.me/cmq1gWbbZsK\">Best Buy</a>, and <a href=\"https://got", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/10/24175355/amazon-echo-pop-smart-speaker-fathers-day-deal-sale", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "You can grab an Echo Pop speaker for $19.99 just in time for Father\u2019s Day", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-10T16:30:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Illustration of the WWDC 2024 logo.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/yeXEXQyRs2H8kZg9E1xhHRx2-do=/20x0:2021x1334/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73399097/STK469_WWDC_2024_B.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>Tim Cook promised that AI features were on the way. At Apple\u2019s Worldwide Developers Conference, we\u2019ll finally learn what Apple\u2019s been building.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/10/24173603/wwdc-2024-live-blog-apple-event-ios-18-ai\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/10/24173603/wwdc-2024-live-blog-apple-event-ios-18-ai", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Live blog: Apple\u2019s AI plans, iOS 18, and more at WWDC 2024", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-10T16:01:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A photo of the Beats Solo 4 wireless headphones.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/W27iyNUxXODJ6dasi95wZNld_5w=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73399034/DSCF7038_3.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>They\u2019re petite, modern, and sound very good, even without dedicated noise cancellation.</em> | Photo by Chris Welch / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"NfIv70\">If you\u2019re still kicking along with the <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2016/12/22/14051984/beats-solo-3-review-apple-headphones\">last-gen Beats Solo</a>, now is a pretty good time to upgrade. It took Apple less than two weeks to discount the 2024 refresh of its alt brand\u2019s on-ear headphones, the <strong>Beats Solo 4</strong>, to $149.95. And now, not even a month later, the price has dropped even further at <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0CZPHPJLN?tag=theverge02-20\" rel=\"sponsored nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Amazon</a>, <a href=\"https://howl.me/", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/10/24175211/beats-solo-4-headphones-oneplus-nord-n30-5g-phone-deal-sale", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The Beats Solo 4 headphones are on sale for their best price to date", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-10T16:00:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Illustration of the WWDC 2024 logo.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/wF4NB7yvsoR9nBjtFVjzyaU4iqk=/20x0:2021x1334/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73399008/STK469_WWDC_2024_D.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p>It\u2019s Apple\u2019s turn to show how AI will work on its iPhones, iPads, and maybe even the Vision Pro.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/10/24171999/apple-wwdc-2024-news-rumors-announcements-ios-18-ai\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/10/24171999/apple-wwdc-2024-news-rumors-announcements-ios-18-ai", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "WWDC 2024: iOS 18 with AI, macOS 15, and more", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-10T15:40:07+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Frontiers illustration\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/JvOsFvwjwU1EAcA3Tmw_mjCmDoA=/107x0:1244x758/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73398984/frontiers.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Bungie</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"X0eHYV\">Bungie just concluded the long-running saga of the light and darkness in <em>Destiny 2: The Final Shape </em>earlier this month<em>, </em>and now the <em>Halo </em>and <em>Destiny </em>developer is teasing what\u2019s next. In a \u201cjourney ahead\u201d stream today, Bungie disclosed the first details on its plans for the rest of the year ahead with <em>Destiny 2</em> and even teased a 2025 release for new content that\u2019s codenamed \u201cFrontiers.\u201d</p>\n<p id=\"7xwVGV\">Until Frontiers arrives next year, <em>Destiny 2</em> will continue with new episodes of story content that explore what\u2019s happened after the conclusion of <em>The Final Shape</em>. <em>Destiny 2</em> players have just battled The Witness in the latest exp", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24175322/bungie-destiny-2-frontier-teaser", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Bungie teases Destiny 2 codenamed \u2018Frontiers\u2019 for 2025", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-10T15:06:37+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Three Pixel watches arranged with the middle one facing the viewer and the other two aiming outward, all with black rubber band straps\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/iL7FETPRwREIjYqHYFio4BkZRwU=/0x0:4320x2880/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73398925/Image.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>These Pixel Watch 3 renders look just like the previous model.</em> | Image: 91mobiles / OnLeaks</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"txYUA0\">Google Pixel Watch 3 renders have apparently leaked, and it looks like not much is changing except for a slightly chunkier design. As <a href=\"https://www.91mobiles.com/hub/google-pixel-watch-3-first-look-renders-exclusive/\">revealed by <em>91mobiles</em></a> and OnLeaks, who <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/5/24/24163867/samsung-galaxy-watch7-ultra-leak-square\">uncovered</a> a rumored \u201cUltra\u201d Galaxy Watch from Samsung last month, the Pixel Watch 3 may arrive with a slightly thicker case to accommodate a", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/10/24175247/google-pixel-watch-3-leak-renders-rumors-41mm", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Leaked Google Pixel Watch 3 renders suggest it will get thicker but not bigger", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-10T14:31:50+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A photo showing Nokia holding a video call with spatial audio\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Rd1pwbyRMwUndrTNXUtEE3t_4sw=/0x0:925x617/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73398841/nokia_spatial_audio_call.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Nokia CEO Pekka Lundmark made the call with Stefan Lindstr\u00f6m, Finland\u2019s ambassador of digitalization and new technologies.</em> | Image: Nokia</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"scFXOg\">Nokia has made the first audio and video call using 3D spatial audio, <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com?id=66960X1514734&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nokia.com%2Fabout-us%2Fnews%2Freleases%2F2024%2F06%2F10%2Fnokia-makes-worlds-first-immersive-voice-and-audio-call%2F&amp;referrer=theverge.com&amp;sref=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2024%2F6%2F10%2F24175231%2Fnokia-3d-spatial-audio-5g-phone-call-advanced\" rel=\"sponsored nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">the company announced</a> on Monday. It placed the call ", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/10/24175231/nokia-3d-spatial-audio-5g-phone-call-advanced", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "This is the \u2018world\u2019s first\u2019 phone call made using spatial audio", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-10T14:30:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Aidan Gomez stares at camera\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/ka9pz3aLckz-wVLQyMFLF8QhZvI=/1x0:2760x1839/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73398831/Aidan_Gomez_Decoder.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo illustration by The Verge / Photo: Cohere</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>Enterprise is the pathway to profit, Gomez says, but maybe don\u2019t ask it to do medicine quite yet.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24173858/ai-cohere-aidan-gomez-money-revenue-llm-transformers-enterprise-stochastic-parrot\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24173858/ai-cohere-aidan-gomez-money-revenue-llm-transformers-enterprise-stochastic-parrot", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "AI will make money sooner than you\u2019d think, says Cohere CEO Aidan Gomez", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-10T12:00:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Vector collage of the Worldwide Developers Conference logo.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/GUUtxhQ81MUdBxuMuiJv634WNCw=/20x0:2021x1334/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73398469/STK469_WWDC_2_2024_A.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"hDuccQ\">We\u2019ve seen two approaches to AI in mobile tech in this year: \u201cAI That\u2019s Not Your Phone\u201d and \u201cAI That Does Random Stuff on Your Phone.\u201d</p>\n<p id=\"T1u21g\">The \u201cNot Your Phone\u201d group includes devices like the Rabbit R1 and the Humane AI Pin, two small gadgets that sought to make AI more useful by building it into a smaller, simpler gadget. It hasn\u2019t gone very well. Both devices came with big promises to help us get things done without looking at our phone screens. <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24126502/humane-ai-pin-review\">Neither</a> <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/5/2/24147159/rabbit-r1-review-ai-gadget\">delivered</a>.</p>\n<p id=\"HYobtK\">", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/10/24171615/apple-ai-siri-wwdc-2024", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Apple\u2019s AI opportunity is all about the big picture", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-10T11:00:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Colorful outline of the Apple logo with WWDC 24 in text below it. Black background.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/cjKJk65Jm067S6fHhSxQOyxTVd8=/0x0:1071x714/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73398411/Apple_WWDC_2024_logo.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Apple</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"cH2wNy\">Apple has a plan for AI, and we\u2019re finally going to hear more than whispers about it <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/3/26/24111331/apple-wwdc-2024-event-date-ai-artificial-intelligence-m4-ios-18\">on June 10th</a> during this year\u2019s Worldwide Developers Conference. If you\u2019re not among the lucky few going to Cupertino, California, to see WWDC 2024 live, you can stream the keynote at 1PM ET on <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RXeOiIDNNek\">YouTube</a>, in the Apple TV app, or <a href=\"https://www.apple.com/apple-events/?useASL=true\">on Apple\u2019s events page</a>.</p>\n<p id=\"U2qrEb\">The company is expected to reveal a <a href", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/10/24171216/apple-wwdc-2024-date-time-how-to-watch", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "How to watch Apple\u2019s 2024 WWDC", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-10T10:08:14+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A cartoon illustration shows a shadowy figure carrying off a red directory folder, which has a surprised-looking face on its side.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/8hgzbwvrfXUwtftGdSeZkvcrZ1I=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73398376/VRG_Illo_STK001_B_Sala_Hacker.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The RansomHub extortion group have claimed responsibility for the cyberattack against Frontier on April 14th.</em> | Illustration: Beatrice Sala</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"6JkVUi\">Frontier Communications has revealed that information for over 750,000 customers \u2014 including full names and Social Security numbers \u2014 was exposed in a data breach following a cyberattack on April 14th. Hackers claim to have even more and will release it unless Frontier pays a ransom.</p>\n<p id=\"mbaH7q\">The attack enabled hackers to access 751,895 customers\u2019 personal data on Frontier\u2019s systems according to a sample of the notice Frontier <a hre", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/10/24175169/frontier-communications-hack-cyberattack-data-breach-ransom", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Frontier hackers threaten to release private data for at least 750,000 customers", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-10T08:19:42+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"An Asus ROG Ally handheld running the Xbox app\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/z1WwtAqdC0M77gIFlW7MthWtvG4=/9x0:2552x1695/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73398305/rogallyxboxapp_twarren.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The Xbox app running on a ROG Ally.</em> | Photo by Tom Warren / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"F5o1u3\">Microsoft\u2019s Xbox chief, Phil Spencer, has been dropping hints about a potential Xbox handheld for months now. Earlier this year he <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/2/15/24073723/microsoft-xbox-next-gen-hardware-phil-spencer-handheld\">said he was \u201ca big fan of handhelds,\u201d</a> after liking posts on X that mention the possibility of this new hardware. Now, in an interview with <em>IGN</em> Spencer says \u201cI think we should have a handheld, too.\u201d</p>\n<p id=\"PiD7KA\">It\u2019s the biggest hint yet that Microsoft is working on an Xbox handheld, something that\u2019s been long-rumored. \u201cThe future for us in hardwar", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/10/24175149/xbox-handheld-phil-spencer-interview-2024", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Xbox boss: \u2018I think we should have a handheld, too\u2019", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-10T07:59:59+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Vector illustration of the Xbox logo.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/M4OhjJiZ-xfVtKOb61Gc91Hsw9o=/20x0:2021x1334/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73398301/STK048_XBOX_C.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"oTkQE7\">Xbox chief Phil Spencer has confirmed that more of Microsoft\u2019s own games will be coming to other platforms, like the PS5 and Nintendo Switch. Microsoft revealed earlier this year that <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/2/15/24073691/microsoft-xbox-games-ps5-nintendo-switch-exclusivity\">four Xbox-exclusive games</a> were launching on PS5 and some on Nintendo Switch, with fans left wondering if it would only be four titles or if there are more to come. Spencer took the opportunity to clear up that mystery in an <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IIpMhthwnto\">interview with <em>IGN</em></a><em> </em>yesterday.</p>\n<p id=\"EW8RmM\">\u201cOur commitment to our Xbox customer", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/10/24174977/xbox-phil-spencer-games-ps5-interview", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Xbox chief confirms more games are coming to other platforms", "user": null, "vote": 0}]